-- Chilean Stock Movers: CCU, Empresas CMPC and Empresas Copec
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2012-01-06T20:56:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-06/chilean-stocks-empresas-cmpc-and-empresas-copec-decline.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Santiago.  The  Ipsa (IPSA)  index rose 0.3 percent to 4,201.48. The  MSCI Chile (MXCL) 
index advanced 0.3 percent to 2,312.17.  Cia. Cervecerias Unidas SA (CCU)  (CCU CC) advanced 2.1 percent to
6,348.5 pesos, leading gains among members of the Ipsa index.
 Chile ’s largest brewer is scheduled to report today preliminary
fourth quarter volumes, according to the company’s website.  Empresas CMPC SA (CMPC)   retreated 0.1 percent to 1,922.3
pesos. Chile’s second-largest pulp exporter said a forest fire
that killed six firefighters and injured two in the country’s
south was started by arsonists, according to a statement e-
mailed yesterday evening.  Empresas Copec SA (COPEC)  , Chile’s largest pulp
exporter, rose 0.3 percent to 6,861.2 pesos. The company’s
plants at the Nueva Aldea complex may resume normal operations
in the coming days, after a forest fire destroyed a $100 million
plywood plant on Jan. 2, Copec said yesterday in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
